definition.value: a pathological bodily process that occurs after a medical intervention. An adverse event is likely caused by the medical intervention; however, such a causal association is not required to be an adverse event.
The OAE official website is: http://www.oae-ontology.org/.
medical intervention is a planned process that has the goal of diagnosing, preventing or relieving illness or injury.
an adverse event that occurs after a vaccination.
an adverse event that has an outcome of abnormal sign in a musculoskeletal or connective tissue.

A musculoskeletal disorder is an injury or disorder of the muscles, nerves, tendons, joints, cartilage, or supporting structures of the upper or lower limbs, neck, or lower back that are caused, precipitated, or exacerbated by sudden exertion or prolonged exposure to physical factors such as repetition, force, vibration, or awkward posture

a behavior and neurological AE that has an outcome of fatigue, which is a state of awareness describing a range of afflictions, usually associated with physical and/or mental weakness, though varying from a general state of lethargy to a specific work-induced burning sensation within one's muscles. Physical fatigue is the inability to continue functioning at the level of one's normal abilities.

A contraindication is a disposition that increases the risk of harm involved in using a particular drug, carrying out a medical procedure, or engaging in a particular activity such that the risk of harm exceeds a threshold. An contraindication serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical treatment.
a planned process that is specifically a test conducted in a clinical laboratory.
a cardiovascular disorder AE that has a cardiac disorder outcome.
an adverse event that occurs in hair, skin, or nail.
a hair, skin, and nail AE that occurs in hair.
a hair, skin, and nail AE that occurs in nail.
a crying abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal inconsolable crying in a patient
a crying abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal unusual high-pitched crying in a patient
a crying abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal prolonged crying in a patient
an adverse event that occurs in the site of a medical intervention (e.g., vaccination injection site).
a site that is used for a medical intervention
convulsion AE is a muscle adverse event that results in a medical condition where body muscles contract and relax rapidly and repeatedly, resulting in an uncontrolled shaking of the body
injection-site induration AE is an skin AE that results in hardening or thickening of tissue at the physical injection site
injection-site pruritus AE is an pruritus AE that results in an unpleasant sensation that evokes the desire or reflex to scratch at the physical area of injection
injection-site rash AE is a rash AE that results in a change of the skin which affects its color, appearance or texture at the physical injection site
injection-site warmth AE is a homeostasis AE that results in feeling of warmth at the physical injection site
A joint disorder AE that has an outcome of joint swelling, which is a joint disorder that results in a buildup of fluid in the soft tissue surrounding the joint
A lymphadenopathy AE that results in swollen/enlarged lymph nodes
a muscle AE that has an outcome of muscular weakness AE (i.e.,  lack of muscle strength).
a sensory capability AE that has an outcome of a sensation of stiffness in muscles and skeleton
nasal congestion AE is a respiratory system AE that results in a blockage of the nasal  passages usually due to membranes lining the nose becoming swollen from inflamed blood vessels

a respiratory system inflammation AE which has an outcome of nasopharyngitis,  a respiratory system inflammation that results in common cold, a contagious, viral infectious disease of the upper respiratory system

a respiratory system inflammation AE which has an outcome of nasopharyngitis, a respiratory system inflammation that results in common cold, a contagious, viral infectious disease of the upper respiratory system
an ear disorder AE which has an outcome of otitis media that results in inflammation of the middle ear, or middle ear infection
pharyngitis AE is a digestive system AE that results in an inflammation of the throat or pharynx
